body:
Louisiana Governor Bobby Jindal said on Tuesday he was suspending his campaign for the Republican nomination for president in 2016, saying it was "not my time."
Jindal, speaking on Fox News, declined to endorse another Republican candidate, saying he would support the party's eventual nominee.

 (Reporting by Emily Stephenson in Washington; Editing by Eric Beech)

title: Republican Louisiana Governor Jindal suspends presidential campaign
